The paper deals with the distributed complexity of the Lovasz Local Lemma, which involves random variables and events. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Graph Theory (cs.GT), or Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The focus on the distributed complexity of the problem suggests that cs.DC is the most likely category, followed by cs.DS and cs.CC. The use of graphs and the Lovasz Local Lemma suggests cs.GT as a possible category, while the mention of probabilities and randomness suggests cs.IT as a possibility.
